  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But what is [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] most significant is that, that they dominated the, the coloration of, of the community.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The community in Kisvarda was very much like any other Orthodox Hungarian community in terms of its organizations and institutions.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was a council, which was, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] by and large, representative of all shades of opinion.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were elected.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The community was officially recognized and the government's power was available to collect what was known as [NON-ENGLISH] Tax, which is [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the official tax that, that everyone had to pay to a religious community, whether Christian or, or Jewish.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This was, by and large, I think, true of all Central European countries, certainly, after the Enlightenment.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The-- out of this-- these taxes, the community, of course, maintained a variety of institutions, starting from the kosher slaughtering of animals and fowl to the rabbis, the cantors, the ritual bath.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was a very large Jewish public school, which I believe went up to either six or eight grades-- I think maybe eight grades.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The school, of course, had to have a core curriculum conforming to the prescribed-- the government-prescribed curriculum.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was relatively little Jewish studies at, at this school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Jewish studies were to be acquired in the-- in the religious schools, the cheders and the Talmud Torah and the yeshiva, which also functioned from time to time, not always, dependent on who the rabbi was.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There were, in the city, I would say, at least two dozen permanent, functioning synagogues.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
